Uninstall gcc-arm-none-eabi
To remove just gcc-arm-none-eabi package itself from Ubuntu 14.10 (Utopic Unicorn) execute on terminal:

sudo apt-get remove gcc-arm-none-eabi
Uninstall gcc-arm-none-eabi and it's dependent packages
To remove the gcc-arm-none-eabi package and any other dependant package which are no longer needed from Ubuntu Utopic.

sudo apt-get remove --auto-remove gcc-arm-none-eabi
Purging gcc-arm-none-eabi
If you also want to delete configuration and/or data files of gcc-arm-none-eabi from Ubuntu Utopic then this will work:

sudo apt-get purge gcc-arm-none-eabi
To delete configuration and/or data files of gcc-arm-none-eabi and it's dependencies from Ubuntu Utopic then execute:

sudo apt-get purge --auto-remove gcc-arm-none-eabi
